{"id":"shobal","term":"Shobal","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>Pilgrim. (1.) The second son of Seir the Horite; one of the Horite “dukes” (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 36:20\">Gen. 36:20</a>).</p>\n<p>(2.) One of the sons of Caleb, and a descendant of Hur (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Chronicles 2:50\">1 Chr. 2:50</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 2:21\">52</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 4:1\">4:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 4:2\">2</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 36:20","1 Chronicles 2:50","Genesis 2:21","Genesis 4:1","Genesis 4:2"]}